  "prompt": "Who is best in Sachin, virat and dhoni?",
  "response": "The debate on who is the best among Sachin Tendulkar, Virat Kohli, and Mahendra Singh Dhoni is subjective and often depends on personal preferences and criteria for greatness. Each of these players has made significant contributions to Indian cricket and has a unique set of achievements:\n\n1. **Sachin Tendulkar**:\n   - Considered one of the greatest batsmen in the history of cricket.\n   - Holds numerous records, including being the highest run-scorer in both ODI and Test cricket.\n   - Played international cricket for 24 years, with 100 international centuries.\n   - Revered for his technique, longevity, and impact on the sport.\n\n2. **Virat Kohli**:\n   - Known for his aggressive batting style and consistency across all formats.\n   - Has one of the highest batting averages in ODIs and Tests among active players.\n   - Has several records for chasing targets and has been pivotal in many of India\u2019s recent successes.\n   - Also served as captain, leading India to significant Test victories and a strong ODI squad.\n\n3. **Mahendra Singh Dhoni**:\n   - Renowned for his leadership, calm demeanor, and finishing abilities.\n   - Led India to victory in the 2007 ICC T20 World Cup, 2011 ICC Cricket World Cup, and 2013 ICC Champions Trophy.\n   - Known for his wicketkeeping skills and innovative tactics.\n   - Widely regarded as one of the best captains in the history of cricket.\n\nUltimately, \"best\" can vary based on whether you're focusing on batting records, leadership qualities, or specific match-winning performances. Each player has left an indelible mark on the game, and fans may favor one over the others based on individual preferences.",
